t others in the guild will be able to help me with the parts that require a group... especially if they also want an item from the same zone... It'd be great if we could combine needs and hit these places for shared benefit rather than just my own.<br>
<br>
To cut a VERY long story short I need to complete 4 tasks for each of 4 different Masters - Illusion, Magic, Charm and Phantasm - in order to get the 4 parts of the Staff of the Serpent. These 'errands' will involve many fun encounters with gods and level 60 mobs as you would expect in such places as Keasora, The Hole, Neriak, PoH and PoF...but that's all way ahead in the future and I don't want to get ahead of myself yet...<br>
<br>
FIRST of all I have to get me a special Enchanters Bag to combine the four staff pieces and in order to get the bag there are three items I have to gather - a Mechanical Pen, Ink of the Dark, and the White Paper.<br>
<br>
To get the Pen out of a little chap in Ak'Anon I have to first give him a Shining Metallic Robe (SMR). This is gonna really hurt me - it's a NICE robe (much better than mine) and I have to give it away to this squirt - sheesh. Anyway, the robe drops off the Arch Ghoul Magi in the Dead Side of Lower Guk. Rare Spawn and Rare Drop. <br>
<br>
To get the Ink I also have to go to Lower Guk. The Ghoul Scribe spawns in the Ghoul Sage room (near the Executioner room). Whilst a rare spawn, this shouldn't be too long a camp. For once I don't have to kill the mob - he will want to kill me, but I have to charm the Scribe and hand him an Empty Ink Vial (I get the vial earlier from some odd lady in Qeynos). <br>
<br>
The white Paper is obtained from some wandering woman with a monk fixation in West Karana. Once I hand her some pretty everyday items a Human Monk named Thrackin Griffen will then spawn at Loc 880, -11570. Kill him and he drops the White Paper. This mob is almost totally magic immune and a tough battle. It is recommended to take a group with some tanks and a cleric.<br>
<br>
So there we have it - two items from Lower Guk and one from West Karana. I will be doing all the 'running around like a crazy thing in a daft dress' over the next week or so, but would like to plan a trip to Guk or WK soon after this. If you're willing to help please let me know here - and if there's an item you want at the same time say what it is so I can plan around it if at all possible.<br>
<br>
